main event: A civilian observed a silver object about the size of a marble in Brooksville, Florida on May 18, 1956.
interesting points: The object made no sound during the observation,The observation lasted for 2 minutes,Initial observation was at 45 degrees elevation, then the object was radar tracked at 90 degrees overhead,The report concluded various possibilities including a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object but was deemed insufficient data to evaluate precisely.
sighted object: a silver round object about the size of a marble
